verses.roman:
prabhura iṅgite govinda prasāda ānilā
purī-bhāratīre prabhu kichu pāṭhāilā

synonyms: prabhura iṅgite—by the indication of Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; govinda—Govinda; prasāda ānilā—brought the remnants of the food of Lord Jagannātha; purī—to Paramānanda Purī; bhāratīre—to Brahmānanda Bhāratī; prabhu—Lord Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; kichu—some; pāṭhāilā—sent.
translation: Following the indications of Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu, Govinda brought the prasāda of Lord Jagannātha. The Lord sent some to Paramānanda Purī and Brahmānanda Bhāratī.
